   influenced the age structure of scraping communities. We assessed
   disease-management strategies by social-network modeling using hunter
   harvests or removal of potential super-spreaders, which fragmented WTD
   social networks reducing the potential spread of disease. Overall, this
   study demonstrates a model capable of predicting potential
   super-spreaders of diseases, outlines methods to locate transmission
   hotspots and community crossroads, and provides new insight for disease
   management and outbreak prevention strategies.},
