   likelihood of tribal engagement increased significantly with the size of
   the AI/AN population, the presence of a tribal facility with Indian
   Health Service funding in the region, and geographic proximity to
   reservation land (p < 0.10). Conclusions The vast majority of public
   health networks do not report engagement with tribal organizations. Even
   when AI/AN serving health facilities are present, reported engagement of
